    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/mitchel_resnick_643061",
        "quote": "Working as a correspondent for 'Business Week,' I felt that I was simply informing people, not empowering them. I saw a parallel problem in the world of education. In too many educational settings, teachers simply 'inform' or 'instruct' learners, rather than providing learners with opportunities to explore, experiment, and express themselves.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Mitchel Resnick",
            "url": "/quotes/mitchel_resnick_643061"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Education",
                "url": "/topics/education"
            },
            {
                "name": "Week",
                "url": "/topics/week"
            },
            {
                "name": "Providing",
                "url": "/topics/providing"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/mitchel_resnick_643058",
        "quote": "In my office, I have the creative things that kids have made for me over the years. The nice thing about the physical side of life is that I can have them on my shelf.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Mitchel Resnick",
            "url": "/quotes/mitchel_resnick_643058"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Over",
                "url": "/topics/over"
            },
            {
                "name": "Side",
                "url": "/topics/side"
            },
            {
                "name": "Made",
                "url": "/topics/made"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/mitchel_resnick_643063",
        "quote": "For me, the most important and distinguishing property of new media is interactivity. But how many people can actually create interactive games, animations, or simulations? Not very many. So, in my mind, very few people are truly literate with new media.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Mitchel Resnick",
            "url": "/quotes/mitchel_resnick_643063"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Very",
                "url": "/topics/very"
            },
            {
                "name": "Distinguishing",
                "url": "/topics/distinguishing"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/mitchel_resnick_643067",
        "quote": "I'm pretty skeptical about a lot of the toys on the market, especially for young kids. Most of them just add these new technologies just to make more flashing lights.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Mitchel Resnick",
            "url": "/quotes/mitchel_resnick_643067"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "New",
                "url": "/topics/new"
            },
            {
                "name": "Pretty",
                "url": "/topics/pretty"
            },
            {
                "name": "Add",
                "url": "/topics/add"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/mitchel_resnick_643069",
        "quote": "Computer programming has been traditionally seen as something that is beyond most people - it's only for a special group with technical expertise and experience. We have developed 'Scratch' as a new type of programming language, which is much more accessible.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Mitchel Resnick",
            "url": "/quotes/mitchel_resnick_643069"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            },
            {
                "name": "Accessible",
                "url": "/topics/accessible"
            },
            {
                "name": "Technical",
                "url": "/topics/technical"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/mitchel_resnick_643071",
        "quote": "With 'Scratch,' our goal is to allow people to mix together all kinds of media, not just sounds, in creative ways. We want people to start from existing materials - grabbing an image, grabbing some sound, maybe even bits of someone else's program, and then extending them and mixing them to make them their own.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Mitchel Resnick",
            "url": "/quotes/mitchel_resnick_643071"
        },
